main_2531383\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qql1665702908064.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qql1665702908064.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qql1665702908064.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qql1665702908064\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Web Security Criteria\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"qql1665702908064__web_security_criteria_127798\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When developing a web application, you need to determine the security criteria the application must meet. Security criteria can vary greatly, depending on the application, the sensitivity of the data it handles, the nature of the industry and the organization itself, and the risks and consequences of security breaches.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qql1665702908064__p_d40826e1_d40827e1_d40828e1\">For example, a banking application will have different criteria than corporate web site that delivers product information. Military and police applications will require different safeguards than a social networking application.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qql1665702908064__p_d40829e1_d40830e1_d40831e1\">When establishing your security criteria, you should consider:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qql1665702908064__li_d20447e1_d20448e1_d20449e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qql1665702908064__p_d40832e1_d40833e1_d40834e1\">Laws and regulations that may be applicable, such as privacy laws.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qql1665702908064__li_d20450e1_d20451e1_d20452e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qql1665702908064__p_d40835e1_d40836e1_d40837e1\">Industry standards that your application processes must comply with.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qql1665702908064__li_d20453e1_d20454e1_d20455e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qql1665702908064__p_d40838e1_d40839e1_d40840e1\">Business risks that you need to avoid, such as\n               compromised safety of people or property, identity misuse, financial risks, loss of\n               reputation.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qql1665702908064__p_d40841e1_d40842e1_d40843e1\">Determine which data needs to be protected and to what degree, where the data resides, and where it crosses boundaries (for example from server to browser, or from server to backend database).</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qql1665702908064__p_d40844e1_d40845e1_d40846e1\">You can use the information and your security criteria in designing and implementing your web application.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qhf1665702908184.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Architecture and Design Considerations for Web Security</a><p>To understand the threats to web security and to help you prevent and counter these threats, you need to understand the processes and components that make up a web application, how the data flows through the application, and the trust boundaries.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531383\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531383\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Web Security Criteria Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Web Security Criteria When developing a web application, you need to determine the security criteria the application must meet. Security criteria can vary greatly, depending on the application, the sensitivity of the data it handles, the nature of the industry and the organization itself, and the risks and consequences of security breaches. For example, a banking application will have different criteria than corporate web site that delivers product information. Military and police applications will require different safeguards than a social networking application. When establishing your security criteria, you should consider: Laws and regulations that may be applicable, such as privacy laws. Industry standards that your application processes must comply with. Business risks that you need to avoid, such as compromised safety of people or property, identity misuse, financial risks, loss of reputation. Determine which data needs to be protected and to what degree, where the data resides, and where it crosses boundaries (for example from server to browser, or from server to backend database). You can use the information and your security criteria in designing and implementing your web application. Related Links Architecture and Design Considerations for Web Security To understand the threats to web security and to help you prevent and counter these threats, you need to understand the processes and components that make up a web application, how the data flows through the application, and the trust boundaries. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}